      <br>
        That <marquee scrollamount="6">he and I</marquee>
					<br>
					<marquee direction="right">should be sitting so</marquee>
<br>
      And sipping a cup of camomile tea.
      <br>
      <br>
      <br>
			<br>
			<br>
			<br>
			<br>

        <font color="white">Light</font> as feathers the witches fly,

      <br>

        The horn of the moon is plain to see;

      <br>
        By a firefly under a jonquil flower

      <br>
        A goblin toasts <marquee direction="right">a bumble-bee.</marquee>

</p>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>

        We might be <font-size:50>fifty</font-size>, we might be five,

        <br>


        So snug,
				<br>
				<marquee>so compact,</marquee>
				<br>so wise are we!
    <br>

        Under the kitchen-table leg
    <br>
        My knee  is pressing <font color="white">against</font color> his knee.
    <br>
      <br>
      <br>
          Our shutters are shut,
					<br>
					the fire is low,
    <br>
        The tap is dripping peacefully;

    <br>
        The saucepan shadows on the wall

      <br>
        Are black and round and plain to see.

      </p>





